dataIdInfo.idPurp: Water Management Areas and Regions used by UK river flow Measuring Authorities that provide data to the National River Flow Archive
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
These regions were compiled from management boundaries provided by Environment Agency (Environment Agency Water Management (or Operational) Region Boundaries at 1:10,000 scale), Scottish Environment Protection Agency (Hydrometry Regions), and other authorities.

Dataset with name 'REGIONS' is always the latest version, older versions have names like 'REGIONS_EXYYYYMMDD' where YYYYMMDD is year, month, and day when it became an old version.

Features in this feature class correspond to Water Management Areas with unique ID in column IDENTIFIER. Water Management Areas are groupped in Water Management Regions with unique ID in columns REG_ID.

Updated by Filip Kral on 12 June 2015 to include latest management areas of the Environment agency and to updare SEPA regions.

Dataset was first created by Filip Kral on 17 March 2014.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.
